---

<Layout title="Logic Ch.8 — Identity and Functions" favicon="🔑">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/logic/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to logic</a>

    <h1>Identity and Functions</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Craig DeLancey &middot; A Concise Introduction to Logic, Ch. 8 &middot; <a href="https://milneopentextbooks.org/a-concise-introduction-to-logic/">CC BY-SA 4.0</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none"><strong>Identity</strong> (=) lets us say two names refer to the same object. Combined with quantifiers, it expresses uniqueness ("there is exactly one") and definite descriptions ("the x such that"). <strong>Functions</strong> in logic map each input to exactly one output.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Elements mapped by a function with identity highlighted -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 340 180" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Domain -->
        <ellipse cx="90" cy="90" rx="60" ry="70" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.3"/>
        <text x="90" y="170" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.35">Domain</text>
